bug.short_desc: Qooxdoo getKeys() implementation is not ECMA 5 compliant, whereas it should be

long_desc.thetext:
Hi, this is a fairly specific bug again (took me hours to track it down to a reproducable sample).
We have an application that we have to deploy inline against Prototype (latest version). This makes all translated strings fail under IE 8 (the labels appear as [Object object]). Non translated strings are fine.
This is probably not very hard to find a workaround if you are familiar with the Qooxdoo code, so I am waiting for someone of the team to look at this (this is showstopper for us :(
The Prototype script used is the vanilla one, latest version, should be 100% compatible with IE 8.
Created attachment 722 Sample app reproducing the problem.
Jean-Noel, could you please tell me your workaround for this? Thanks.

I am not the one in charge of this bug on our side, Jean-Noel is, but in order to gain time, since Jean-Noel is in Vancouver, I'll answer that I am pretty sure he hasn't a workaround yet. The bug is showing up in our current release, sadly making it unusable under IE8.
Vincent, thank you for the answer.
I tested the attached application and it seems to me that this issue occurs on all IEs (IE6, IE7 and IE8) not only on IE8. Vincent, could you please verify this.
I just checked on our deployed application and the bug does indeed appear on IE7. I tried to check on IE6 but since our editor doesn't support IE6 it won't even load and I can't test it.
Thanks very much for this in-depth analysis.

I spent much time today on this, and contacted some people familiar with Prototype. I now understand better what happens and I think I will have a workaround (loading Prototype after Qx is not possible for us).
However, Prototype folks looked at your Object.keys implementation and told me it was not ES5 compliant, so this should probably be fixed on your side. I will return with more info on that later. (Note that Prototype's implementation is not ES5 compliant either, which causes the bug).
Jean-Noel, thank you for testing! We will have a look after the 1.1 release. The change is too critical to change this near completion, without intensive testing.
Fixed on trunk (1.2) with rev. 22171 and branch (1.1.x) with rev. 22174.
